y Separation Technology and Membranes Soft Matter Surface Science Water Treatment The BS in Chemical Engineering program offers expertise in a wide variety of areas  including thermodynamics  separation processes  transport phenomena  reactor design  combustion  and process control  Students may use elective courses to specialize in these and other areas  Further  BS in Chemical Engineering provides an excellent curriculum to prepare medical school aspirants  and for further study at the graduate level  As the only chemical engineering department at a public university in the Chicago metropolitan area  this program provides unique opportunities for students to interact with world class industries through research projects and internship programs medical school aspirants I  Program Requirements A  Degree Requirements Degree Requirements Degree Requirements Curriculum Flowchart Curriculum Flowchart  B  Special Programs  BS in Chemical Engineering  Biochemical Engineering Concentration  Students in this concentration complete the following   students in the concentration will be required to take a minimum of     semester hours for the degree  For more information Honors Program  After they have been admitted to UIC  all incoming freshmen with an ACT composite score of at least    or an SAT total score of       and who rank in the top    percent of their high school class  are invited to join the Honors College  membership is not automatic  students must submit an application   Honors College  II  How to Apply A  Entrance Requirements First Year Students First Year Students  Transfer  Readmit  Transfer  Readmit B  Admissions View Application Deadlines View Application Deadlines Frequently Asked Questions Frequently Asked Questions C  Financial Aid and Scholarship View Financial Aid and Scholarship Details View Financial Aid and Scholarship Details Apply Now The Department of Chemical Engineering offers a program leading to the Master of Science and to the Doctor of Philosophy in Chemical Engineering  The primary areas upon which these fields are based are continuum and molecular fluid mechanics  heat and mass transfer  macroscopic and microscopic thermodynamics  chemical kinetics  and process analysis  Application areas include energy production and utilization  material properties under extreme conditions  biologically based processes  and the environment Master of Science Doctor of Philosophy I  Program Requirements A  MS Thesis  Project  Course Work Only  n Degree Requirements n  Degree Requirements B  PhD  n Degree Requirements n  Degree Requirements C  Special Programs  n    China Program  MS in Chemical Engineering  n     China Program  MS in Chemical Engineering  nChemistry and Other Majors Can Apply for MS PhD in Chemical Engineering n Chemistry and Other Majors Can Apply for MS PhD in Chemical Engineering II  How to Apply A Graduate Program  The department reviews each applicant on an individual basis  Complete transcripts of all undergraduate and any graduate work must be submitted  In addition to meeting the Graduate College minimum requirements  applicants must meet the following program requirements  Baccalaureate Field  Engineering or Chemistry Grade Point Average  At least           for the final    semester hours     quarter hours  of undergraduate study  and at least      for the doctoral program  In exceptional cases  applicants with averages below      but above      may be admitted on limited standing if they show evidence of substantial ability to complete the program successfully Tests Required   ETS institution code       GRE general Minimum English Competency Test Score  TOEFL     with subscores of Reading     Listening     Speaking     and Writing     iBT Internet based  OR IELTS      with subscores of     for all four subscores  OR PTE Academic     with subscores of Reading     Listening     Speaking     and Writing     OR Recommendation Letters    required Personal Statement  Required B  Admissions Gener